==English==
===Etymology===
From [[dear]] + -est, superlative-forming suffix

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-dearest.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
'''dearest'''
# superlative degree of [[dear]]; most dear

====Quotations====
* So I, made lame by fortune's '''dearest''' spite, / Take all my comfort of thy worth and truth. &mdash; William Shakespeare, ''Sonnet XXXVII''

===Noun===
'''dearest'''
# (''term of endearment'') a beloved person

